<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n05032h"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05032h">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05032h"> 32(h)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> devil in human form</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><mark>The devil, in human form</mark>, accosted him in a street one day and asked him where he was going. &lsquo;I go where God calls me,&rsquo; said Martin. &lsquo;Know then,&rsquo; said the Adversary, &lsquo;that go where you may, do what you will, I will constantly oppose you.&rsquo; <small> Margaret Maitland, <a name="MMLL" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#MMLL"><cite title="source">Life and Legends of St. Martin of Tours (316-397)</cite></a> (1908) 22</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
